verbs.description: unstick (third-person singular simple present unsticks, present participle unsticking, simple past and past participle unstuck)

entries.meaning: (transitive, sometimes figurative) To free from the condition of being stuck.
(intransitive) To become freed from a stuck condition.
examples: Starting to panic, I stepped back and put my foot right through the door. Outside, Nelson laughed. The door unstuck. I hopped on one leg as it swung outward, carrying my boot.

entries.meaning: (intransitive, aviation, of an aircraft) To leave the ground during takeoff.
